A £4.8 million programme of building refurbishment work has started in West Dunbartonshire. £4.8m work will upgrade three blocks A £4.8 million programme of building refurbishment work has started in West Dunbartonshire.The local council has appointed contractors Lovell to carry out the work on three 15-storey blocks of flats in Clydebank.The high-rises - West, Clyde, and Park Court, all at Littleholm Place - contain some of 270 flats.Work has just begun on the year-long scheme, which will include the installation of insulated overcladding to the tower blocks' upper walls. 